tafsir[14]{c,v,t}:
  74,48,"Then will no intercession of (any) intercessors profit them."
  74,49,"Then what is the matter with them that they turn away from admonition?-"
  74,51,"Fleeing from a lion!"
  75,1,"I do call to witness the Resurrection Day;"
  75,2,"And I do call to witness the self-reproaching spirit: (Eschew Evil)."
  75,3,"Does man think that We cannot assemble his bones?"
  75,5,"But man wishes to do wrong (even) in the time in front of him."
  75,6,"He questions: \"When is the Day of Resurrection?\""
  75,8,"And the moon is buried in darkness."
  75,10,"That Day will Man say: \"Where is the refuge?\""
  75,11,"By no means! No place of safety!"
  75,15,"Even though he were to put up his excuses."
  75,16,"Move not thy tongue concerning the (Qur'an) to make haste therewith."
  75,17,"It is for Us to collect it and to promulgate it:"